    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-08-13T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-08-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="135"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d135">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">868.01/18: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The High Commissioner at Constantinople</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bristol</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Constantinople</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-08-13">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 13, 1920</hi>
                        </date>.<lb/>[Received August 16—7:22 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>449. Following from Smyrna: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“August 13, noon. I have just had notification from the Greek High
                            Commission that the treaty clauses<note n="12" xml:id="d135fn12">Treaty
                                of Sèvres, Aug. 10, 1920.</note> will be carried out as from
                            yesterday; that the Ottoman officials are superseded by Greek
                            authorities; that the transfer of government commenced yesterday and
                            that relations between the new authorities and foreign representatives
                            will be carried out through the Greek High Commission. Government
                            building, Custom House and <hi rend="italic">gendarme</hi> stations were
                            taken last night without opposition and Ottoman officials superseded.
                            Despatch will be forwarded. Russell.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bristol</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
